<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,152,1144]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,886,912]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leme &amp; L. Kollmann" authorityYear="2011" box="[402,727,887,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="santaleopoldinensis">
<emphasis box="[402,727,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Vriesea santaleopoldinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Leme (1999: 163)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="163" authorityYear="1999" box="[969,1304,886,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rafaelii">
<emphasis box="[969,1083,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">V.rafaelii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[1091,1304,886,912]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="135 - 168" refId="ref22365" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (1999) New Species of Brazilian Bromeliaceae: A Tribute to Lyman B. Smith. Harvard Papers Botany 4 (1): 135 - 168." type="journal article" year="1999">Leme (1999: 163)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the leaf blades that bear dense and minute wine spots near the base (vs. green with darker green longitudinal lines and not spotted), by peduncle bracts densely wine spotted (vs. without spots), floral bracts reaching 1/3 of sepal length (vs. reaching 1/2 of sepal length) and densely white spotted (vs. without spots). The flowers are more numerous (ca. 27 vs. ca. 
<quantity box="[795,854,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
number) with longer pedicels (ca. 
<quantity box="[1269,1353,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 
<quantity box="[151,233,1080,1106]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long), wine spotted sepals (vs. without spots) and by the petals with a narrowed apex and longer basal appendages (ca. 
<quantity box="[345,427,1118,1144]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 
<quantity box="[516,598,1118,1144]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
long).
</paragraph>
